<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910517-0033</DOCNO><DOCID>910517-0033.</DOCID><HL>   Jones Apparel Stock   Holds Closely to Price   Of Initial Offering</HL><DATE>05/17/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7B</SO><CO>   JNY</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>TEXTILES AND APPAREL (TEX)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)</IN><NS>STOCK andamp; OTHER MARKET NEWS (STK)</NS><RE>NEW YORK (NY)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Jones Apparel Group Inc. shares, which begantrading yesterday after the company's initial public offeringof 5.6 million common shares, held closely to the $14offering price.   Of the 5.6 million shares, 4.2 million are being offeredby the company and 1.4 million by selling shareholders. Netproceeds will be used to repay short-term debt, among otherthings.</LP><TEXT>   Jones Apparel makes women's wear, primarily under theJones New York label. Its shares closed yesterday at $14.50,down 50 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading.   The offering is being made through an underwritingsyndicate managed by Merrill Lynch andamp; Co. A registrationstatement covering the offering was filed with the Securitiesand Exchange Comission last month.</TEXT></DOC>